name: Easy Chicken Enchilada Soup
author: Gregory Chapman
summary: Pressure cooker or slow cooker! Super easy set-it-and-forget-it meal, with all the enchilada taste in a soup. Garnish with cilantro, avocado, red onion, shredded cheese, sour cream, and tortilla strips or chips.
ingredients: 2 pounds skinless, boneless chicken breast halves
2 (14 ounce) cans black beans, rinsed and drained
1 (15 ounce) can whole kernel corn, drained
1 (14 ounce) can fire-roasted diced tomatoes, with juice
directions: Combine chicken breasts, black beans, chicken stock, corn, tomatoes, enchilada sauce, green chiles, onion, garlic, salt, and cumin in a multi-functional pressure cooker
Select Stew mode and cook on high pressure according to manufacturer's instructions; set timer for 30 minutes
Allow 10 to 15 minutes for pressure to build
Release pressure using the natural-release method according to manufacturer's instructions, 10 to 40 minutes
Remove chicken, shred it with 2 forks, and return it to the soup
